# Deobfuscated Code Analysis

## Step-by-step Deobfuscation

The code uses several obfuscation techniques:
1. **String array with Base64 encoding** - `a0_0x525d()` returns an array of Base64-encoded strings
2. **Lookup function** - `a0_0x5085()` decodes and caches strings
3. **Control flow flattening** - `switch` statements with scrambled case orders (`"0|4|2|1|3"`)
4. **Dead code/decoy branches** - fake `if/else` paths that never execute
5. **Proxy functions** - objects wrapping simple arithmetic (`function(a,b){return a*b}`)

## Deobfuscated Code

```javascript
// Constants
const TAU = 6.283;          // ~2π
const PHI = 1.618;          // Golden ratio
const SQRT_HALF = 0.707;    // ~√(1/2)

// Simulation configuration
const config = {
    yield: 4000,             // Repulsion strength between nodes
    leverage: 0.004,         // Spring stiffness default
    volatility: 0.92,        // Velocity damping factor (friction)
    liquidity: 0.0003,       // Centering force strength
    portfolio: 40,           // Max number of particles
    correlation: 0.04,       // Particle drag/friction
    delta: 0.06              // Camera smoothing factor
};

// Nodes (graph vertices)
const nodes = [
    { id: "hub",     label: "Hub",     r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "alpha",   label: "Alpha",   r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "beta",    label: "Beta",    r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "gamma",   label: "Gamma",   r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "delta",   label: "Delta",   r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "epsilon", label: "Epsilon", r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// Edges (springs connecting nodes)
const edges = [
    { a: "hub",   b: "alpha",   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
    { a: "hub",   b: "beta",    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
    { a: "hub",   b: "gamma",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "hub",   b: "delta",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "hub",   b: "epsilon", rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "beta",    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "gamma", b: "delta",   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "epsilon", rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// Camera state
let camera = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
let cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// Particle system
let particles = [];
let frameCount = 0;

// Find a node by ID
function findNode(id) {
    for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
    }
    return null;
}

// Physics simulation step
function applyForces() {
    // 1. Node-to-node repulsion (Coulomb's law style)
    for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        for (let j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
            let dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
            let dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
            let dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
            let force = config.yield / (dist * dist);
            let fx = (dx / dist) * force;
            let fy = (dy / dist) * force;
            nodes[i].vx += fx;
            nodes[i].vy += fy;
            nodes[j].vx -= fx;
            nodes[j].vy -= fy;
        }
    }

    // 2. Spring forces along edges (Hooke's law)
    for (let i = 0; i < edges.length; i++) {
        let nodeA = findNode(edges[i].a);
        let nodeB = findNode(edges[i].b);
        if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;

        let dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
        let dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
        let dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        let displacement = dist - edges[i].rest;
        let force = (edges[i].k || config.leverage) * displacement;

        nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
    }

    // 3. Apply velocity: damping, centering, integration
    for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        // Centering force (pulls toward 400, 300)
        nodes[i].vx += (400 - nodes[i].x) * config.liquidity;
        nodes[i].vy += (300 - nodes[i].y) * config.liquidity;

        // Friction/damping
        nodes[i].vx *= config.volatility;
        nodes[i].vy *= config.volatility;

        // Position integration
        nodes[i].x += nodes[i].vx;
        nodes[i].y += nodes[i].vy;
    }
}

// Spawn a new particle from a random node
function spawnParticle() {
    if (particles.length >= config.portfolio) return;

    let angle = Math.random() * TAU;
    let sourceNode = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
    let speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT_HALF;

    particles.push({
        x: sourceNode.x,
        y: sourceNode.y,
        vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
        vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
        age: 0,
        maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
        size: 0.8 + Math.random() * PHI * SQRT_HALF
    });
}

// Update all particles
function updateParticles() {
    for (let i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        let p = particles[i];

        // Apply drag
        p.vx *= 1 - config.correlation * 0.125;
        p.vy *= 1 - config.correlation * 0.125;

        // Move
        p.x += p.vx;
        p.y += p.vy;

        // Age and remove expired
        p.age++;
        if (p.age > p.maxAge) {
            particles.splice(i, 1);
        }
    }
}

// Smooth camera movement
function updateCamera() {
    camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * config.delta;
    camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * config.delta;
    camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.delta;
}

// Main loop
function tick() {
    applyForces();
    updateParticles();
    updateCamera();
    frameCount++;
    if (frameCount % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();
}

setInterval(tick, 16); // ~60 FPS
```

## What It Does

This is a **force-directed graph simulation** — essentially a physics engine for laying out a network graph. Here's the summary:

### Core Mechanics
| Component | Description |
|---|---|
| **Nodes** | 6 labeled nodes (Hub, Alpha, Beta, Gamma, Delta, Epsilon) with positions and velocities |
| **Repulsion** | All nodes repel each other (inverse-square law, like electric charges) |
| **Springs** | Connected nodes are attracted via spring forces (Hooke's law) with rest lengths |
| **Damping** | Velocity is multiplied by 0.92 each frame (friction to prevent chaos) |
| **Centering** | A weak force pulls everything toward (400, 300) |
| **Particles** | Decorative particles spawn from random nodes, drift outward, and die after a lifespan |
| **Camera** | Smoothly interpolates toward a target position using lerp with factor 0.06 |

### The Big Picture

This is the **simulation/physics backend** for an animated, interactive network visualization (likely rendered on an HTML canvas elsewhere). The financial-sounding parameter names (`yield`, `leverage`, `volatility`, `portfolio`, `correlation`, `liquidity`, `delta`) are purely cosmetic obfuscation — they're just physics constants dressed up in finance jargon. The code runs at ~60 FPS with no rendering — it only computes positions, suggesting a separate render loop reads the `nodes`, `particles`, and `camera` state.
